# SEO Standards

## Meta Tags (via generateMetadata)
- Every page MUST have unique `title` and `description`
- Title format: `[Page Name] | Zap It Pest & Termite Control Melbourne`
- Suburb pages: `Pest Control [Suburb] | Zap It Pest & Termite Control`
- Titles: 50-60 chars max, descriptions: 140-155 chars max
- Include `openGraph` and `twitter` card metadata
- Set `alternates.canonical` on every page

## Schema / JSON-LD
- Generate ALL schema from `lib/schema.ts` — one source of truth
- Homepage: WebSite + Organization + LocalBusiness + Product/AggregateRating + FAQPage
- Suburb pages: LocalBusiness + FAQPage (from `faq_json` column)
- Service pages: Service schema + FAQPage
- Blog posts: Article schema with author, datePublished, dateModified
- Never duplicate schema types on the same page
- Use `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` for JSON-LD `<script>` tags

## Technical SEO
- Dynamic XML sitemap via `app/sitemap.ts` — include ALL published pages
- `app/robots.ts` — allow all, point to sitemap
- 301 redirects in `next.config.ts` (20 redirects from SEO workbook)
- `<link rel="canonical">` on every page
- Structured breadcrumbs with BreadcrumbList schema

## Images
- ALL images must have descriptive `alt` text — never empty
- Use next/image with WebP format, quality 80
- Max 100KB per image after optimization
- Use `sizes` prop for responsive images

## Internal Linking
- Every suburb page links to parent region + 2-3 nearby suburbs
- Every service page links to related services
- Blog posts link to relevant service/suburb pages
- Use descriptive anchor text, never "click here"

## NAP Consistency
- Phone: `03 9126 0555` (primary, consistent everywhere)
- Address: `80 Porter Rd, Heidelberg Heights, VIC 3081, Australia`
- Name: `Zap It Pest & Termite Control Melbourne`
